General.Name: Guideline Geo AB (publ)
General.Description: Guideline Geo AB (publ) provides sensors, software, services, and support for mapping and visualizing subsurface for use in detecting and mapping groundwater, environmental and geological risk assessments, infrastructure site investigations, and mineral exploration. The company offers ABEM Terrameter LS 2, a resistivity and IP surveying system; ABEM Terraloc Pro 2, a seismograph for geotechnical and structural assessment, geological survey, and environmental studies; ABEM WalkTEM 2, a rapid survey solution for the search, mapping and monitoring of groundwater, mineral deposits, and environmental change; ABEM Terrameter SAS 1000, a geophysical instrument for vertical electrical sounding applications; and ABEM Terrameter Log 3000, a plug-and-play borehole logging tool. It also provides MALÅ Easy Locator Core, a ground penetrating radar solution; MALÅ GroundExplorer, an integrated GPR solution with a range of antenna options and measuring devices; MALÅ MIRA HDR, a 3D GPR array for mapping large areas to locate buried objects and artefacts; MALÅ Easy Locator Widerange, a dual antenna choice for utility mapping; MALÅ GeoDrone 80, an airborne GPR solution; MALÅ 3D Imaging Radar Array, a one-pass 3D system for large-scale mapping and subsurface object identification; MALÅ ProEx, a GPR solution; and MALÅ Concrete Explorer, a GPR system designed for concrete investigations and non-destructive imaging of man-made structures. In addition, the company software solutions. The company was formerly known as Guideline Technology AB (publ) and changed its name to Guideline Geo AB (publ) in June 2013. Guideline Geo AB (publ) is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
